This paper is primarily focused on face detection using fully convolutional neural networks (FCN), which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel method for accelerating FCN-based face detection with higher accuracy, which involves attention mechanisms and masked-convolution operations, indicating that it could also fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves experiments and evaluations of the proposed method, which could also fall under the multimedia (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories.
